"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-lifestyle-celeb-news-local-celebs-mama-joy-paris-olympics-renaldo-gouws-da-suspension-latest\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbLifestyle\\u00bbCeleb News\\u00bbLocal Celebs\\u00bb'Happiest woman in the world': Mama Joy celebrates Renaldo Gouws downfall  No-one standing in her way to Paris Olympics? Mama Joy is celebrating the suspension of her biggest critic, Renaldo Gouws\\u2026  Joy Chauke, or Mama Joy, is celebrating the downfall of disgraced DA MP Renaldo Gouws, who was suspended from the party following a clip of his racist rant from 2010.  The sports fan has been tweeting up a storm about her biggest critic, including reposting several shady tweets.  The outspoken social media commentator has criticised Chauke over herreceiving multiple government-sponsored tripsto attend events abroad. Chauke has hinted that she will be attending the Paris Olympics next month.  The Summer Olympics, which will take place from 26 July to 11 August in Paris, France.  In a since-deleted tweet, Mama Joy said of Renaldo Gouws' suspension: \\\"I am the happiest woman in the whole world. Guys, I told you, you can not talk about Mama Joy, and nothing happens. Do you believe it?\\\".  Chauke has also been retweeting many tweeps calling Gouws \\\"disgusting\\\" and \\\"bigoted\\\".  The sports fan's tweet comes a day after she met DA leader John Steenhuisen at the Union Buildings during the presidential inauguration. In a clip, Steenhuisen said: \\\"I am here with our favourite Mama Joy. I want to thank you for bringing the World Cup trophy back where it belongs, here to South Africa\\\".  Steenhuisen added: \\\"On to the Olympics next.\\\"  Mama Joy cheekily captioned the clip: \\\"Not even \\u2066Renaldo Gouws\\u2069 will stop me to go to the Olympics\\\".  In a showdown on X last week, Gouws said of Chauke's ambitions to go to Paris: \\u00a0\\\"Snowball's chance in hell. Unless you pay your own way\\\".  He added: \\\"Gravy Train has derailed. She can work and earn a salary and then use that money to travel the world.  Last year, Gouws - viaAfriForum -demanded the department reveal information behind Mama Joy's trip to the Rugby World Cup. The investigation revealed that over R1 million had been spent to send both Mama Joy and fellow fan Botha Msila to France, which included flights, accommodation, and other expenses.  While the Department of Sports, Arts, and Culture has yet to confirm if it will sponsor Mama Joy's trip to the Olympics, it would not be the first time she has attended the games.  In 2016, Chauke was invited to travel with the South African team to Brazil for the Rio Olympics.  She toldIOL:\\\"When (Gauteng Sport MEC) Faith Mazibuko told me that I was going to Rio for the Olympics, I was so happy.\\\"  Chauke was gifted four stunning outfits by SA designer Sun Goddess to wear to the games.  According toThe Star,Mama Joy was also gifted a full Bafana Bafana supporters gift, a pair of new takkies, and money.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"